description: Silwan Community Development through the Establishment of the Europ House

subproject.corporate outcome:
- Civic engagement, through civil society organizations, voluntary associations, trade unions, political parties, and private sector organizations, enables all people to influence public policy processes. 
- Electoral laws, processes and institutions strengthen inclusive participation and professional electoral administration 
- Communication channels support government accountability and transparency through e-governance, independent journalism, and access to information policies
subproject.description: The project will contribute to economic and Social welbeing in Silwan Community by promoting women's active participation in social, economical and political life as well as environmental awareness of the local community that suffers from unhealth environmental conditions.  the intervention will focus mainly on Women and Youth of Silwan Community in General, women in particular
subproject.gender code: Gender equality as a significant objective
